import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming you have a DataFrame 'df' with a column 'product category'
df['product category'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='coral', edgecolor='black')

# Set font sizes for various elements
plt.title('Count of Products by Category', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Category', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Number of Products', fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=10)  # Rotate and set font size for x-axis labels
plt.title('Average Product Weight by Category', fontsize=14)
plt.xlabel('Average Weight (g)', fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel('Category', fontsize=12)

# Set font size for x-axis labels and rotate them for better readability
plt.xticks(fontsize=6, rotation=90)

plt.show()
